[SN]TITLE[SN]
Funeral to be held for Steve Taylor, former BBC and HTV journalist

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The funeral of former HTV and BBC Wales journalist Steve Taylor has been held.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Mr Taylor, who was a regular face presenting the news, died in December aged 65.
His roles at the BBC included presenting the Four-Five-Six programme on BBC Radio Wales.
His funeral was held at Holy Trinity, Christchurch, in Newport, and was followed by a service at the Gwent Crematorium in Croesyceiliog. Mr Taylor leaves a wife and two children.
As well as his work at the BBC, Mr Taylor was a presenter and journalist at HTV, the predecessor of ITV Wales.
He also presented on BBC Radio Gwent and worked for the Newport-based South Wales Argus newspaper.
